Criteria for appointment of primary procurators

People who meet the criteria specified in Article 75 of this Law and have the following conditions may be appointed as the primary procurator of the People's Procuracy;If you are a military officer in the army, you can be appointed as a primary procurator of the Military Procuracy:

1. Having time for legal work for 04 years or more;

2. Having the capacity to practice the right to prosecute and control judicial activities;

3. The exam has been admitted to the elementary procurator rank.

Criteria for appointing intermediate procurators

1. People who meet the criteria prescribed in Article 75 of this Law and meet the following conditions may be appointed as an intermediate procurator of the People's Procuracy;If you are a military officer in the army, you may be appointed to the Intermediate Procurator of the Military Procuracy:

a) As a primary procurator for at least 05 years;

b) Having the capacity to practice the right to prosecute and control judicial activities;

c) Ability to guide the practice of prosecution rights, control judicial activities for primary procurators;

d) Performed exams for the secondary procurators.

2. In case of the needs of the People's Procuracy, the person who has had time to do legal work for 10 years or more, has the criteria prescribed in Article 75 of this Law, Points B,c and d, Clause 1 of this Article may be appointed to the Intermediate Procurator of the People's Procuracy;If you are a military officer in the army, you may be appointed to the Intermediate Procurator of the Military Procuracy.

