Oath of procurators

The person appointed to the procurators must sworn:

1. Absolutely loyal to the Fatherland, dedicated to serving the people;

2. Uncontracted struggle with all criminals and violations of law;

3. Resolutely protect the constitution, law, reason and social justice;

4. Constantly striving, studying and following the teachings of President Ho Chi Minh "Cong Minh, integrity, objectivity, caution, humility";

5. Strictly observing discipline and principles of organization of activities of the People's Procuracy.

Procurator dismiss

1. Procurators are naturally dismissed from the title of Procurator when convicted by the judgment of the Court, which has taken legal effect.

2. Depending on the nature and seriousness of the violation, Procurators may be dismissed from the title of procurators when one of the following cases:

a) Violation while practicing the right to prosecute and control judicial activities;

b) Violation of the provisions of Article 84 of this Law;

c) Violation of ethical qualities;

d) There are other violations of law.

