a) Study the case, work and reporting records to the Procurator;

b) Making records of incident and tasks;

c) Helping procurators to perform other activities when practicing the right to prosecute and control judicial activities;

d) Perform other duties and powers as assigned by the Director.

5. Inspectors take responsibility before the law, before the Procurator and before the Director of the People's Procuracy for the performance of their duties and powers;If there is a violation of the law, depending on the nature and seriousness of the violation, it is disciplined, administratively handled or examined for penal liability.

