1. Organizations and individuals conducting oil and gas activities must establish safe areas around the oil and gas project.

2. Safety areas around the oil and gas project on the sea include:

a) Forbidden zones for oil and gas projects at sea, except for underground works, is the area determined by a radius of 500 meters from the outer edge of the works on all sides including the location.anchoring for floating and mobile facilities, except for special cases decided by the Prime Minister;

b) Forbidden areas of anchoring or underground activities under the sea are the area determined within 02 nautical miles from the outer edge of the oil and gas project including underground works under the seabed;Vehicles and boats must not be anchored or underground activities on the sea floor, except for special cases approved by the contractor or the Prime Minister decided.

3. Safety area around the oil and gas project is a safe area determined around the works and equipment for oil and gas activities on the mainland, depending on the geographical and social conditions ofThe place of oil and gas activities, for the purpose of ensuring safety for people and vehicles in the process of implementing oil and gas activities.

4. Organizations and individuals conducting petroleum activities must perform the following work of ensuring oil and gas safety:

a) Develop documents on safety management, including safety management programs, risk assessment reports, emergency rescue plans to submit to competent state management agencies for approval;

b) Establish, maintain and develop safety management systems to ensure risk control of risks in the entire oil and gas activities;

c) Establish and maintain an effective emergency response system, minimize damage when incidents and accidents occur harmful to people, environment or property;

d) Equipped with a warning system that is likely to detect bad situations that can occur dangerous to works, environment and automatically notify and information to the Executive Center for the above oil and gas works.The sea has no people working often;

d) There is a duty ship to ensure timely rescue in case of emergency for petroleum works at sea with people working regularly.The operator of oil and gas activities in neighboring mines or lots of oil and gas can coordinate the use of shared ships but must ensure that there is a continuous ships for timely rescue in an emergency.

5. The Government details this.

Rights and obligations of the basic investigation organization about oil and gas

1. Organizing the basic survey of oil and gas with the following obligations:

a) Compliance with the approved project content;

b) Ensuring honesty and adequity in collecting and synthesizing documents and information about petroleum geology;Information security in the process of basic investigation of oil and gas;

c) Protection of minerals and other resources in the process of basic investigation of oil and gas;

d) Submit reports on basic surveys on oil and gas to the Ministry of Natural Resources and Environment for updates to the national database system of geology and minerals.

2. Organizing the basic survey of petroleum has the right to transfer abroad, the documents obtained during the basic investigation of oil and gas, the types of objects with the amount and type suitable to the properties.and requirements for analyzing and handling tests under the approved project and compliance with the provisions of the law on the protection of state secrets and other relevant laws.

3. Organizations outside the state -owned agencies and enterprises conducting basic surveys on oil and gas have the rights specified in Clause 2 of this Article and the following rights:

a) Manage the exploitation and use of information, data and basic survey results on oil and gas under the approved agreement;

b) Use information according to documents security commitment, proposed to revoke expenses when participating in bidding, signing oil and gas contracts at the oil and gas lot in the area that has undergone basic surveys under the Scheme.

Form of contractor selection

The selection of contractors to sign petroleum contracts at the Oil and Gas open lot is made through one of the following forms:

1. Spacious bidding;

2. Limited bidding;

3. Hello competitive bid;

4. Contractor appointment.

Contractor selection plan

1. The contractor selection plan is made for one or several oil and gas batches on the list of oil and gas batches approved in accordance with Clause 2, Article 7 of this Law to implement the selection of contractorsOil and gas contract.

2. The main content of the contractor selection plan includes:

a) The list of oil and gas lots and the form of contractor selection for each oil lot;

b) Preliminary assessment of the oil and gas potential of each lot of oil and gas;

c) Procedure time;

d) Criteria for selecting contractors;

d) The evaluation method.

Spacious bidding

1. The selection of contractors to sign petroleum contracts in the form of spacious bidding is applied on the principle of competition for oil and gas lots not in the case specified in Articles 19, 20 and 21 of this Law..

2. The spacious bidding process includes the following steps:

a) Notice of bid invitation;

b) Bid registration;

c) Issuing bidding documents;

d) Receive bids, bid opening and evaluation of bids;

d) Evaluation, approval and notice of contractor selection results and basic economic and technical conditions of oil and gas contracts;

e) Negotiate and finalize oil and gas contracts;

g) Evaluation, approval and signing of oil and gas contracts.

Hello Competition

1. The selection of contractors to sign petroleum contracts in the form of competitive bidding is applied in case the oil and gas lot is not included in the existing contractor selection plan and proposed by at least 02 groupsofficials and individuals who are eligible for Article 16 of this Law to sign a oil and gas contract.

2. Competitive bidding process includes the following steps:

a) Notice of competitive bidding;

b) Register to participate in the competitive bid;

c) Issuing competitive bidding invitations;

d) Receive documents and evaluate competitive bidding documents;

d) Evaluation, approval and notice of contractor selection results and basic economic and technical conditions of oil and gas contracts;

e) Negotiate and finalize oil and gas contracts;

g) Evaluation, approval and signing of oil and gas contracts.

Appoint contractors

1. The selection of contractors to sign petroleum contracts in the form of contractor appointment applies to oil and gas lots in the following cases:

a) Regarding national defense and security;

b) Only one organization or individual eligible for the specified in Article 16 of this Law proposes to sign a oil and gas contract after being widely informed within 30 days but no other contractors are interested in;

c) The contractor is performing the petroleum contract to propose additional investment in the same contract area with economic and technical conditions for the new oil and gas contract after the oil and gas contract has been signed expiry.

2. Contractor appointment process includes the following steps:

a) Issuing a dossier for contractor appointment;

b) Receive proposals and evaluate the proposal;

c) Evaluation, approval and notice of contractor selection results and basic economic and technical conditions of oil and gas contracts;

d) Negotiate and finalize oil and gas contracts;

d) Evaluation, approval and signing of oil and gas contracts.

Approving the contractor selection results

The contractor is proposed to choose when meeting the following conditions:

1. Bids, competitive bidding documents, valid proposals;

2. Meeting the requirements of capacity and experience of oil and gas activities;

3. Meet technical requirements;

4. Meet economic requirements;

5. Having bids, competitive bidding documents are first ranked.

Organize contractor selection

1. Vietnam Oil and Gas Group has the following responsibility:

a) Making a plan for contractor selection, reporting to the Ministry of Industry and Trade for appraisal and submitting it to the Prime Minister for approval;

b) Notice of bidding invitations or competitive bidding;issuing bidding documents, competitive bidding invitations or bidding requests;organize the evaluation of bids, competitive bidding documents or proposals;

c) Report the results of contractor selection for the Ministry of Industry and Trade to appraise and submit to the Prime Minister for approval;

d) Notice the results of contractor selection and basic economic and technical conditions of oil and gas contracts, organize negotiations and complete the contents of oil and gas contracts, report to the Ministry of Industry and Trade to appraise and submitThe Prime Minister approved as a basis for signing oil and gas contracts.

2. The Government stipulates the dossiers, order and procedures for selecting contractors to sign oil and gas contracts.

Grant investment registration certificate

1. On the basis of the signed petroleum contract, the Ministry of Industry and Trade granted an investment registration certificate for the contractor to conduct oil and gas activities.

2. The main content of the investment registration certificate includes:

a) Name of oil and gas contract, oil and gas, oil and gas project;

b) Objectives and scale;

c) Places;

d) Executive office;

d) Contractors, the ratio of benefits and operators;

e) The minimum financial commitment of the petroleum exploration phase;

g) The contractor's responsibility for finance, technology and self -bearance;

h) The rights of the contractor may revoke expenses from oil and gas production in accordance with the provisions of the oil and gas contract;

i) The term of oil and gas contract;

k) Effective date of oil and gas contract.

3. The Government stipulates the documents, order and procedures for granting investment registration certificates.

The main content of the oil and gas contract

1. The main content of the oil and gas product division contract includes:

a) Legal status and benefits of contractors signing contracts;

b) The object of the contract;

c) Limit the area and progress of returning the contract area;

d) Effect of contracts, contract terms, stages of contracts, conditions for extending the stages and adjustments and extension of the contract term;

d) Rights and obligations of contracts and operators;

e) Minimum work commitment and minimum financial commitment according to the contract stage;

g) Principle of dividing oil and gas products and determining recovery costs;

h) Principles of selecting contractors providing oil and gas and goods for oil and gas activities;

i) Rights of the host country for assets and petroleum works after recovery of expenses and after termination of the contract;

k) Conditions for transfer of the rights and obligations of the contracting parties;

l) The rights of the Vietnam Oil and Gas Group are entitled to the contract when there is a trade detection and the priority is given to buy the rights to participate, the rights and obligations that the contractor transfer in the contract when transferred;

m) Commitment to commissions, training, scientific research funds and priority for use of Vietnamese labor and services;

n) Responsibility to protect the environment and ensure safety while conducting oil and gas activities;obligations to collect oil and gas works;

o) Conditions for termination of contracts, handling violations;

p) The dispute settlement method arises from the contract and the law applies.

2. The Prime Minister shall decide the main content of other oil and gas contracts in accordance with the characteristics of the mine, mine clusters, and oil and gas.

3. The Government promulgates the sample contract of the oil and gas product division contract.

Cost recovery in oil and gas contract

Participants of oil and gas contracts may agree on the contractor's expense recovery in the oil and gas contract in accordance with the following provisions:

1. Maximum of 50% of oil and gas production can be exploited during the year for oil and gas contracts applied to conventional oil and gas batches;

2. Maximum of 70% of oil and gas production in the year for oil and gas contracts applied to lots and petroleum fields are entitled to investment incentive policies;

3. Maximum of 80% of the oil and gas production in the year for oil and gas contracts applied to lots and petroleum fields are entitled to special investment preferential policies.

Lập, phê duyệt chương trình hoạt động và ngân sách hoạt động hằng năm

1. Căn cứ vào các cam kết trong hợp đồng dầu khí và chương trình, kế hoạch đã được phê duyệt (nếu có), nhà thầu lập chương trình hoạt động và ngân sách hoạt động hằng năm trình Tập đoàn Dầu khí Việt Nam phê duyệt.

2. Nội dung chính của chương trình hoạt động và ngân sách hoạt động hằng năm bao gồm:

a) Nội dung công việc;

b) Dự toán chi phí;

c) Kế hoạch sử dụng nhân lực.

Lập, thẩm định, phê duyệt chương trình tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí

1. Trong giai đoạn tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí, trên cơ sở quy định trong hợp đồng dầu khí, nhà thầu lập chương trình tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí trình Tập đoàn Dầu khí Việt Nam thẩm định, phê duyệt.

2. Nội dung chính của chương trình tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí bao gồm:

a) Tổng quan về hợp đồng dầu khí;

b) Lịch sử tìm kiếm thăm dò, thẩm lượng, phát triển và khai thác dầu khí (nếu có);

c) Tài liệu về địa chất, địa vật lý, tài liệu khoan, tài liệu khảo sát và nghiên cứu khác;

d) Đặc điểm địa chất, hệ thống dầu khí, đánh giá tài nguyên dầu khí;

đ) Tiến độ thực hiện, khối lượng công việc, dự toán chi phí;

e) Kế hoạch thực hiện công tác an toàn và bảo vệ môi trường bao gồm cả an toàn và xử lý sự cố, giải pháp ngăn chặn và xử lý các nguy cơ gây ô nhiễm;

g) Dự kiến kết quả đạt được, đánh giá rủi ro tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí;

h) Kết luận và kiến nghị.

3. Nội dung thẩm định chương trình tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí bao gồm:

a) Đánh giá sự phù hợp của tài liệu về địa chất, địa vật lý, tài liệu khoan, tài liệu khảo sát và nghiên cứu khác;

b) Đánh giá tính hợp lý của số liệu về đặc điểm địa chất, hệ thống dầu khí, đánh giá tài nguyên dầu khí;

c) Đánh giá tính khả thi, hợp lý của tiến độ thực hiện, khối lượng công việc, dự toán chi phí;

d) Đánh giá sự đáp ứng yêu cầu về an toàn và bảo vệ môi trường;

đ) Đánh giá kết quả đạt được và các rủi ro tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí.

4. Trong trường hợp có sự thay đổi các nội dung chính của chương trình tìm kiếm thăm dò dầu khí quy định tại khoản 2 Điều này, nhà thầu đề nghị điều chỉnh chương trình, trình Tập đoàn Dầu khí Việt Nam thẩm định, phê duyệt.

5. Trong quá trình phát triển mỏ dầu khí, khai thác dầu khí, nhà thầu có thể đề xuất tiến hành thăm dò dầu khí bổ sung và lập chương trình thăm dò dầu khí bổ sung, trình Tập đoàn Dầu khí Việt Nam thẩm định, phê duyệt theo quy định tại khoản 2 và khoản 3 Điều này.

Evaluation, evaluation and approval of resource statements, oil and gas reserves

1. On the basis of the results of the exploration and jurisdiction of oil and gas, if the oil and gas is detected in the area of ​​oil and gas contracts, the contractor makes a statement of natural resources and oil reserves submitted to the Petroleum GroupMale reported the Ministry of Industry and Trade to appraise and approve.

2. The main contents of the resource and oil reserves report include:

a) History of search and exploration, quantity, development and exploitation of oil and gas;

b) DOCUMENTATION SEOSE SEASONS AND METHODS OF DELIVERY;drilling documents;survey documents and other research;

c) regional geology, mine geology;

d) Parametric parameters include geological formation of oil and gas, geophysical geophysics, mine technology, exploitation results, oil pressing pumps, gas and water (if any);

d) Calculating oil and gas on the initial spot, oil and gas reserves of oil and gas and petroleum detection;

e) Conclusion and recommendation.

3. The content of evaluation of resources and oil reserves includes:

a) Assess the results of the exploration and examination of oil and gas;

b) Geological rationality, geological model of pavement container, container parameters and mine technology;

c) The rationality and reliability of the initial petroleum calculation results and oil and gas reserves.

4. Vietnam Oil and Gas Group is responsible for monitoring, synthesizing resources, oil and gas reserves of oil and gas fields in Vietnam and updated annually information on resources and oil reserves reportingMinistry of Industry and Trade.

5. The contractor is responsible for updating the statements of the resources and gas reserves of each mine within 03 years from the date of oil, the first gas to be exploited and then updated for 05 years..In case the total amount of oil and gas on the first spot has changed more than 15% compared to the nearest approval, the contractor makes a report of resources and oil reserves updated to submit to the Vietnam Oil and Gas Group to report to the Ministry of Industry and Trade.Consider and approve in accordance with this Article.

6. The Government stipulates dossiers, order, procedures, appraisal and approval of resource and gas resources statements.

Establishing, evaluating and approving the Old Petroleum Development Plan

