Domestic violence

1. Domestic violence acts include:

a) Torturing, mistreating, beating, threatening or other intentional acts to abuse health and life;

b) Instant, lead or other intentional acts insulting honor and dignity;

c) Forced to witness violence against people and animals in order to put frequent psychological pressure;

d) Leave and care;Do not nurture and take care of family members who are children, pregnant women, women who are raising children under 36 months of age, elderly people, people with disabilities, people who are unable to take care of themselves;do not educate family members as children;

d) Discrimination and discrimination of physical shape, gender, gender and capacity of family members;

e) Prevent family members from meeting relatives, have legal, healthy social relations or other behaviors in order to isolate and put frequent psychological pressure;

g) Prevent the exercise of rights and obligations in family relationships between grandparents and grandchildren;between father, mother and child;between husband and wife;between siblings and sisters;

h) Revealing or distributing information about private life, personal secrets and family secrets of family members to insult the honor and dignity;

i) Forced to perform acts of contradictory sex of spouse;

k) Forced to perform porn behavior;Forced sound, view images, read pornography, stimulate violence;

l) Forced child marriage, marriage, divorce or obstructing marriage, legal divorce;

m) Forced pregnancy, abortion, fetal sex selection;

n) appropriate and destroy the common property of the family or private property of other family members;

o) Forcing family members to study, overwork, and contribute their financial contributions;Control assets and income of family members in order to create physical, mental or other aspects;

p) Isolate and detain family members;

Q) Forced family members out of illegal legal accommodation.

2. The acts specified in Clause 1 of this Article shall be performed between the divorced person;people living as husband and wife;He is a father, mother, stepchild, siblings, and younger sisters who have divorced, of the people living as husband and wife;People who have had a adopted parents' relationship with each other are also identified as a domestic violence in accordance with the Government's regulations.

International cooperation on domestic violence prevention and control

1. International cooperation on domestic violence prevention and control is implemented on the principle of equality, respect for independence and sovereignty, in accordance with Vietnamese law and international law.

2. Contents of international cooperation on domestic violence prevention and control include:

a) Participate in international organizations;signing and implementing international treaties and international agreements on domestic violence prevention and control;

b) Develop and implement programs, projects and activities on domestic violence prevention and control;

c) Exchange of information and experience on domestic violence prevention and control;

d) Scientific research, human resource training on domestic violence prevention and control.

Rights and responsibilities of people with domestic violence

1. People with domestic violence have the following rights:

a) Requesting competent agencies, organizations and individuals to protect health, life, honor, dignity, other legitimate rights and interests related to domestic violence;

b) Request competent agencies and individuals to apply measures to prevent, protect and support in accordance with this Law;

c) To be arranged in a temporary place, keep a secret about the temporary shelter and information about private life, personal secrets and family secrets in accordance with this law and other relevant laws.;

d) Be provided with medical services, psychological advice, skills to respond to domestic violence, legal aid and social assistance in accordance with the law;

dd) Request those who commit domestic violence to overcome the consequences and compensate for health damage, honor, dignity and property damage;

e) Be information about relevant rights and obligations in the process of resolving conflicts and disputes among family members, handling domestic violence acts;

g) Complaints, denunciations and lawsuits for violations of the law on domestic violence prevention and control;

h) Other rights in accordance with the law related to domestic violence prevention and control.

2. People with domestic violence, guardian or legal representative of people with domestic violence are responsible for providing adequate, accurate and timely information related to domestic violence acts.When required by competent agencies, organizations and individuals.

The responsibility of the person who commits domestic violence

1. People who commit domestic violence are responsible:

