The exercise of citizens' freedom of residence

1. Citizens exercising the freedom of residence in accordance with this Law and other provisions of relevant laws.

2. The exercise of citizens' freedom of residence is only limited in the following cases:

a) Persons who are carried out by the authorities and persons who are subject to prohibited measures from leaving their residence and detention measures;The person sentenced to imprisonment but has not had a judgment execution decision or has made a judgment execution decision but is on bail or has been postponed the execution of the sentence, suspending the judgment execution;Prison sentenced people are entitled to suspended sentences during the challenge;people who are serving sentences for imprisonment, prohibited residence, probation or non -custodial reform;people who are released from prison ahead of time are in the time of challenges;

b) People who are serving educational measures in communes, wards and townships, measures to be taken to compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments and put them into reformatory schools;people must abide by measures to be taken to compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments, taken to reformatory but are being postponed or temporarily suspended from observance;The manager during the time of examining and deciding on the application of measures to put into compulsory educational institutions, put into compulsory detoxification establishments, and put them into reformatory schools;

c) People are isolated from the risk of spreading disease to the community;

d) Locations and areas of isolation due to disease prevention and control according to decisions of competent agencies and people;areas with emergency conditions in accordance with law;The location is not allowed to register for new permanent residence, new temporary residence registration, separation of households in accordance with this Law;

