Rights and obligations of citizens in accessing information

1. Citizens have the right:

a) To provide complete, accurate and timely information;

b) Complaints, lawsuits and denunciations of violations of the law on information access.

2. Citizens are obliged:

a) Comply with the provisions of the law on information access;

b) Do not falsify the information content provided;

c) Failing to infringe upon the legitimate rights and interests of agencies, organizations or others when exercising the right to access information.

Phạm vi và trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin

1. Cơ quan nhà nước có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do mình tạo ra, trừ trường hợp quy định tại Điều 6 của Luật này; đối với trường hợp quy định tại Điều 7 của Luật này thì cung cấp thông tin khi có đủ điều kiện theo quy định.

Ủy ban nhân dân cấp xã có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do mình tạo ra và thông tin do mình nhận được để trực tiếp thực hiện chức năng, nhiệm vụ, quyền hạn của mình, trừ trường hợp quy định tại Điều 6 của Luật này; đối với trường hợp quy định tại Điều 7 của Luật này thì cung cấp thông tin khi có đủ điều kiện theo quy định.

2. Cơ quan nhà nước trực tiếp tổ chức thực hiện việc cung cấp thông tin, trừ các trường hợp sau đây:

a) Văn phòng Quốc hội có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Quốc hội, cơ quan của Quốc hội, cơ quan thuộc Ủy ban thường vụ Quốc hội, Hội đồng bầu cử quốc gia tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

b) Văn phòng Chủ tịch nước có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Chủ tịch nước tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

c) Văn phòng Chính phủ có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Chính phủ, Thủ tướng Chính phủ tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

d) Văn phòng Đoàn đại biểu Quốc hội có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Đoàn đại biểu Quốc hội tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

đ) Văn phòng Hội đồng nhân dân cấp tỉnh có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Hội đồng nhân dân, Thường trực Hội đồng nhân dân, các cơ quan của Hội đồng nhân dân cấp tỉnh tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

e) Văn phòng Ủy ban nhân dân cấp tỉnh có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Ủy ban nhân dân, Chủ tịch Ủy ban nhân dân cấp tỉnh tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

g) Văn phòng Hội đồng nhân dân và Ủy ban nhân dân cấp huyện có trách nhiệm cung cấp thông tin do Hội đồng nhân dân, Thường trực Hội đồng nhân dân, các cơ quan của Hội đồng nhân dân, Ủy ban nhân dân, Chủ tịch Ủy ban nhân dân cấp huyện tạo ra và thông tin do mình tạo ra;

h) Ủy ban nhân dân cấp xã có trách nhiệm cung cấp cho công dân cư trú trên địa bàn thông tin do mình và do các cơ quan ở cấp mình tạo ra, thông tin do mình nhận được để trực tiếp thực hiện chức năng, nhiệm vụ, quyền hạn; cung cấp cho công dân khác thông tin này trong trường hợp liên quan trực tiếp đến quyền và lợi ích hợp pháp của họ;

i) Bộ trưởng Bộ Quốc phòng, Bộ trưởng Bộ Công an quy định đầu mối thực hiện cung cấp thông tin trong hệ thống tổ chức của mình.

Information must be public

1. The following information must be widely publicized:

a) Legal documents;Administrative documents have general applicable value;The international treaty that the Socialist Republic of Vietnam is a member and international agreement that Vietnam is one side;administrative procedures, work settlement processes of state agencies;

b) Common information, guiding the implementation of laws, regimes and policies for areas under the management of state agencies;

c) Draft legal documents in accordance with the law on promulgating legal documents;Content and results of referendum, absorbing people's opinions on issues under the decision competence of state agencies and giving people's opinions in accordance with the law;Projects and draft projects to establish, dissolve, enter and divide administrative units, adjust the administrative boundaries;

d) Strategy, programs, projects, schemes, plans and plannings for socio -economic development of the nation and localities;Planning sectors, fields and methods, implementation results;annual work programs and plans of state agencies;

d) Information on state budget estimates;report on the implementation of the State budget;State budget settlement;estimates, implementation and settlement of budgets for programs and projects on capital construction investment using state budget capital;State budget procedures;

e) Information on allocation, management and use of official development support capital and non -governmental aid sources as prescribed;information on management and use of social relief and social benefits;manage and use the contributions of people and funds;

g) Information about the list of projects, public investment programs, public procurement and management and use of public investment capital, situation and results of implementation of public investment plans, programs and projects;Bidding information;information on land use plannings and plans;land price;land acquisition;Plan for compensation, site clearance and resettlement related to projects and works in the area;

h) Information on investment, management and use of state capital at enterprises;Report on evaluation of operational results and enterprise classification;The report on supervision of the implementation of the financial information of enterprises and state agencies representing the owner;information about organization and operation of state -owned enterprises;

i) Information about products, goods and services has a negative impact on health and environment;Conclusion of inspection, inspection and supervision related to environmental protection, community health, food safety, labor safety;

k) Information on functions, tasks, powers and organizational structure of agencies and attached units;duties and powers of cadres and civil servants directly settle the tasks of the people;rules and regulations promulgated by state agencies;

l) Periodic work reports;Annual financial reports;statistical information about industry and field;National database of industry and field;Information on recruitment, use and management of cadres, civil servants and public employees;Information about the list and results of the program, scientific topic;

m) The list of information must be publicized according to the provisions of Point b, Clause 1, Article 34 of this Law;Name, address, phone number, fax number, email address of the state agency or the focal person to receive the request to provide information;

n) Information related to public interests and health of the community;

o) Information on taxes, fees and fees;

p) Other information must be made public in accordance with the law.

2. In addition to the information specified in Clause 1 of this Article, based on the actual conditions, the State agency proactively publicizes other information created or held by them.

Form, time of information disclosure

1. Types of information disclosure include:

a) Published on the web portal, the website of the state agency;

b) Publicly on the mass media;

c) Publishing Official Gazette;

d) Listed at the headquarters of state agencies and other locations;

d) Through the reception of citizens, press conferences, press releases, activities of spokesperson of state agencies in accordance with law;

e) Other forms that are favorable for citizens shall be determined by the agency.

2. In case the law has provisions on the form of publicity for specific information, it is applied.

In case the law does not specify the form of information disclosure, based on the actual conditions, the state agency is responsible for providing information that can choose one or some forms of information disclosure.Determined in Clause 1 of this Article guarantee for citizens to access information.

3. For those who are disabled, people living in the border, islands, mountainous areas, areas with extremely difficult socio -economic conditions, in addition to the forms prescribed in Clause 1Hey, state agencies determine the form of information in accordance with the ability and conditions to access information of citizens.

4. The time of public information for each field is implemented in accordance with the relevant law;In case the law has not been prescribed, at the latest, 05 working days from the date of creating information, the competent state agency must publicize the information.

Publicize information on the web portal, websites

1. In the information specified in Article 17 of this Law, the following information must be made public on the web portal, website:

a) Legal documents;The international treaty that the Socialist Republic of Vietnam is a member and international agreement that Vietnam is one side;administrative procedures, work settlement processes of state agencies;

b) Common information, guiding the implementation of laws, regimes and policies for areas under the management of state agencies;

c) Strategies, programs, projects, schemes, plans and socio -economic development plannings of the nation and localities;Planning sectors, fields and methods, implementation results;annual work programs and plans of state agencies;

d) Information about the list of projects, programs and results of public investment, public procurement and management and use of public investment capital, loan capital sources;

d) Information on functions, tasks, powers, organizational structure and organizational diagrams of agencies and attached units;Address, phone number, fax number, email address of the state agency, the focal point of receiving the request to provide information;

e) Annual financial statements;statistical information about industry and field;Information about the list and results of the program, scientific topic;

g) The list of information must be made public, which must clearly state the address, form, time and time limit for each type of information;

h) Information if deemed necessary for public benefits and health of the community;

i) Other information prescribed by law on the web portal, websites.

2. The disclosure of information on the web portal and websites in provinces and cities directly under the Central Government shall comply with the information technology application plan of the provincial People's Committee.

3. State agencies responsible for providing information in accordance with this Law are responsible for storing records and documents that have been imported into the list and must be classified in the way and forms of facilitation.ensuring citizens' access to information;Ensuring information can be electronic storage, must be digitized for an appropriate time limit and to open for people to approach;At the same time, it is necessary to connect to electronic networks nationwide to easily access from different systems.

4. Electronic portal, websites of state agencies must be linked, integrated with the web portal, websites of the affiliated agencies to update information and create favorable informationBeneficial for citizens in finding and exploiting information.

5. In addition to the information specified in Clause 1 of this Article, based on the actual conditions, the State agency proactively posted other information created by themselves on the website and web portal.

6. In case the state agency does not have an electronic portal and an electronic information page, based on the actual conditions, it is responsible for publicizing the information specified in Clause 1 of this Article in another appropriate form..

The form of information requirements

1. The requester may request to provide information in the following forms:

a) Directly or authorize others to go to the headquarters of state agencies to request information.

The recipient of the request is responsible for guiding the person who requests to fill out the contents specified in Clause 2 of this Article in the request for information provision.

In case the person requesting to provide illiterate information or disability cannot write the request, the recipient of the request to provide information is responsible for filling the contents to the request form for information provision;

b) Send a request voucher voucher voting on electronic network, postal service, fax to the information provider.

2. The request for information provision must be expressed in Vietnamese including the following main contents:

a) Full name;residence, address;identity card number, citizen identity card or passport number of the requesting person;fax number, phone, email address (if any);

b) The information is required to provide, which specifies the names of documents, records and documents;

c) The form of information provision;

d) Reasons and purposes required information.

3. In case of request for information provision specified in Clauses 1 and 2, Article 7 of this Law, the written consent of individuals and organizations shall be enclosed.

4. The Government stipulates the form of information required for information.

Từ chối yêu cầu cung cấp thông tin

1. Cơ quan nhà nước từ chối cung cấp thông tin trong các trường hợp sau đây:

a) Thông tin quy định tại Điều 6 của Luật này; thông tin không đáp ứng điều kiện quy định tại Điều 7 của Luật này;

b) Thông tin được công khai theo quy định tại Điều 17 của Luật này, trừ trường hợp quy định tại khoản 1 Điều 23 của Luật này;

c) Thông tin được yêu cầu không thuộc trách nhiệm cung cấp;

d) Thông tin đã được cung cấp hai lần cho chính người yêu cầu, trừ trường hợp người yêu cầu có lý do chính đáng;

đ) Thông tin được yêu cầu vượt quá khả năng đáp ứng hoặc làm ảnh hưởng đến hoạt động bình thường của cơ quan;

e) Người yêu cầu cung cấp thông tin không thanh toán chi phí thực tế để in, sao, chụp, gửi thông tin qua dịch vụ bưu chính, fax.

2. Trường hợp từ chối cung cấp thông tin, cơ quan nhà nước phải thông báo bằng văn bản và nêu rõ lý do.

The responsibility of the information provider in ensuring the exercise of information access

1. State agencies are responsible for providing information specified in Article 9 of this Law is responsible:

a) Publicize and provide information in a timely, accurate and complete manner;In case of detection of information provided inaccurate or incomplete, it is required to correct or provide additional information;

b) Proactively set up, update and publicize the information portfolio must be publicized and posted the list on the web portal, websites;regularly update and disclose information at the right time, term and form according to the list of information must be made public;

c) Maintain, store and update the information database responsible for providing, ensuring systematic, complete, comprehensive, timely and easy information;

d) Ensure the accuracy and complete information of information.The transfer of information between data systems is implemented in accordance with the law;

d) Technical guidance on information protection measures and processes and protection of information management systems;

e) Review, classify, check and ensure the confidentiality of information before providing;

g) Timely consider and consider the benefits of providing information to disclose information or provide information on request to ensure public interests and health of the community;

h) Promulgate and publicize the internal regulations on the organization providing information within the scope of their responsibilities, including the following main contents: Determining the focal point to provide information;the transfer of information of the unit created to the focal point of information provision;The classification of information is provided and not provided;Update information publicly, information provided as required;The order and procedures for processing the requirements of providing information between the focal unit and the unit in charge of information databases and relevant units;

i) Review the provisions of the law on access to information related to their functions, tasks and powers to promptly propose to the competent state agency amended and supplemented to comply with.This law;

k) Settlement of complaints, complaints, denunciations and handling of violations of access to information in accordance with law;

l) Report to the competent state agency on the situation of ensuring the right to access information of citizens at their agency when required.

2. The head of the unit assigned to be the focal point to provide information is responsible for ensuring the performance of the task of providing information of the agency, promptly processing the information provider under the management competence with the execution.Vi obstructed the right to access information of citizens.

3. Persons assigned to provide information are responsible for providing timely and adequate information to citizens;Do not harass, obstruct, difficult during the task.

Responsibilities of the Government, ministries, ministerial -level agencies, government -attached agencies and People's Committees at all levels in ensuring the implementation of information access rights

1. The Government unified state management of the work of ensuring the implementation of citizens' rights of information access and the following tasks and powers:

a) Promulgating according to its competence or proposing competent state agencies to promulgate, amend, supplement and improve the law on information access;

b) Stipulating measures to create favorable conditions for people with disabilities, people living in border areas, islands, mountainous areas, areas with extremely difficult socio -economic conditions to exercise the right to accessbelieve;

c) Implement dissemination and education to raise awareness about the rights and responsibilities of agencies, units, cadres, civil servants, officials and citizens in exercising the right to access information;

d) Guide agencies, organizations, units and citizens in exercising information access rights;

d) Inspection and examination of law enforcement, handling of violations of laws on information access;

e) Technical guidance on measures, information preservation processes and information management systems;

g) Monitor, urge and inspect the implementation of citizens' right to access to information.

2. The ministries, ministerial -level agencies and government -attached agencies shall base themselves on the functions and tasks that are responsible for performing the tasks prescribed at Points a, c, d, dd and g, Clause 1 of this Article.

3. The Ministry of Information and Communications helps the Government to perform the tasks specified at Point e, Clause 1 of this Article.

4. The Ministry of Justice helps the Government to monitor the implementation of this Law.

5. The provincial People's Committee is responsible for state management in the area, implementing measures to ensure the right to access to citizens' information under the Government's instructions.

6. State agencies shall base themselves on their actual conditions, enabling the person to directly read, view, listen, record, copy and take documents at the headquarters;Equipped with information sheets or other equipment to disclose information.

Measures to protect network security

1. Measures to protect network security include:

a) Appraisal of network security;

b) Assessing network security conditions;

c) Cyber ​​security inspection;

d) Monitoring network security;

d) Response and overcome network security incidents;

e) Struggling to protect network security;

g) Use passwords to protect network information;

h) Preventing and requiring suspension, stopping network information;suspend, suspend activities of establishing, supplying and using telecommunications networks, internet, manufacturing and using radio broadcasting and broadcasting equipment in accordance with the law;

i) Request to remove and access illegal information or false information in cyberspace infringing on national security, social order and safety, legal rights and interests of the agency., organizations and individuals;

k) Collecting electronic data related to the activities of infringing upon national security, social order and safety, legitimate rights and interests of agencies, organizations and individuals on cyberspace;

l) blockade and limit the operation of the information system;suspend, suspend or request to stop operating of information systems, recover domain names in accordance with law;

m) Prosecution, investigation, prosecution and trial in accordance with the Criminal Procedure Code;

n) Other measures as prescribed by law on national security and law on handling of administrative violations.

2. The Government stipulates the order and procedures for the application of network security protection measures, except for the measures specified at Points m and n, Clause 1 of this Article.

International cooperation on network security

1. International cooperation on cybersecurity is carried out on the basis of respect for independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity, not interfering with each other's internal affairs, equality and mutual benefits.

2. Content of international cooperation on network security includes:

a) Research and analyze network security trends;

b) Develop mechanisms and policies to promote cooperation between Vietnamese organizations and individuals and foreign organizations and individuals and international organizations operating on cybersecurity;

c) Sharing information and experience;support training, equipment and technology to protect network security;

d) Preventing and combating cybercrime, acts of infringing upon network security;Preventing risks of cyber security;

d) Consulting, training and developing cybersecurity human resources;

e) Organize international conferences, seminars and forums;

g) Signing and implementing international treaties and international agreements on cybersecurity;

h) Implementation of international cooperation programs and projects on cybersecurity;

i) Other international cooperation activities on cybersecurity.

3. The Ministry of Public Security is responsible to the Government to assume the prime responsibility for, coordinate with the implementation of international cooperation on cybersecurity, except for international cooperation activities of the Ministry of Defense.

The Ministry of Defense is responsible to the Government to perform international cooperation on cybersecurity within the scope of management.

The Ministry of Foreign Affairs is responsible for coordinating with the Ministry of Public Security and the Ministry of Defense in international cooperation activities on cybersecurity.

In case of international cooperation on cybersecurity, it is related to the responsibilities of many ministries and branches decided by the Government.

4. International cooperation activities on cybersecurity of other ministries, branches and localities must have written participation in the opinion of the Ministry of Public Security before implementing and eliminating international cooperation activities of the Ministry of Defense.

Acts of being strictly prohibited on cybersecurity

1. Use cyberspace to perform the following behavior:

a) Acts specified in Clause 1, Article 18 of this Law;

b) Organize, operate, conclude, instigate, bribe, deceive, entice, train and train people against the State of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam;

c) Misradation of history, denying revolutionary achievements, destroying the great unity bloc of the entire nation, insulting religion, discriminating against gender, racism;

d) False information causes confusion among the people, causing damage to socio -economic activities, making it difficult for the activities of state agencies or officials on duty, infringing upon rights and interestslegitimate of other agencies, organizations and individuals;

d) Prostitution, social evils, and human trafficking;posting lewd, depraved and crime information;destroying the traditions and customs of the nation, social morality, the health of the community;

e) incite, entice and incite others to commit crimes.

2. Performing cyber attacks, network terrorism, network spy, cyber criminals;causing incidents, attacks, intrusion, accounting for control, deviation, interruption, stagnation, paralysis or destroying important information systems on national security.

3. Producing and putting into use tools, means, software or obstructing behaviors, causing disorders of operating of telecommunications networks, internet, computer networks, information systems, processing systemsand control information and electronic means;Dispersing informatics programs that are harmful to the activities of telecommunications networks, Internet, computer networks, information systems, processing and control systems, electronic media;Illegally invading telecommunications networks, computer networks, information systems, information processing and control systems, databases, electronic means of others.

4. against or hinder the operation of network security forces;Attacking and disabling the law, losing the effect of protecting network security.

5. Taking advantage or abuse of cybersecurity activities to infringe on sovereignty, interests, national security, social order and safety, legitimate rights and interests of agencies, organizations and fishmultiply or to profit.

6. Other acts violate the provisions of this Law.

Important information system on national security

1. The important information system on national security is the information system when incidents, intrusion, occupying control, false, interruption, stagnation, paralysis, attack or destruction will beserious infringement of network security.

2. Important national security information system includes:

a) Military, security, diplomatic and cipher systems;

b) The information system for storing and processing information belongs to state secrets;

c) The information system for preserving and preserving artifacts and documents of particularly important value;

d) The information system for preserving materials and substances is particularly dangerous for humans and ecological environment;

d) The information system for preserving, manufacturing and managing other particularly important facilities related to national security;

e) Important information systems for activities of agencies and organizations at the central government;

g) National information system in the field of energy, finance, banking, telecommunications, transportation, natural resources and environment, chemicals, health, culture and press;

h) Automatic control and supervision system at important works related to national security, important goals on national security.

3. The Prime Minister promulgates, amends and supplements the list of important information systems on national security.

4. The Government stipulates the coordination between the Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of Defense, the Ministry of Information and Communications, the Government Cipher Committee, the ministries and functional agencies in the evaluation, evaluation, inspection and supervision, responding and troubleshooting for important information systems on national security.

Cyber ​​security evaluation for important national security information systems

1. Cyber ​​security evaluation is an activity to consider and evaluate the contents of cybersecurity as a basis for the decision to build or upgrade the information system.

2. Subjects of network security appraisal for important information systems on national security include:

a) The pre -feasibility study report, the design dossier of construction of investment projects to build the information system before approval;

b) Project on upgrading the information system before approval.

3. Content of network security evaluation for important information systems on national security includes:

a) Compliance with network security regulations and conditions in design;

b) In accordance with the plan of protecting, responding, troubleshooting and arranging manpower to protect network security.

4. The authority to evaluate network security for important information systems on national security is prescribed as follows:

a) Forces in charge of network security protection under the Ministry of Public Security appraise cybersecurity for important information systems on national security, except for the case specified at Points b and c this Clause;

b) Forces in charge of cybersecurity protection under the Ministry of Defense appraising cybersecurity for military information systems;

c) The Government Cipher Committee appraised network security for the cipher information system of the Government Cipher Committee.

Assessing network security conditions for important national security information systems

1. Assessing the conditions of cybersecurity is an activity to consider the network security response of the information system before putting into operation and use.

2. Important information systems on national security must meet the following conditions about:

a) Regulations, processes and plans to ensure network security;operating personnel, system administration;

b) Ensuring cybersecurity for equipment, hardware and software are system components;

c) Technical measures to monitor and protect network security;Measures to protect the control system and automatic monitoring, Internet of things, real -actual - virtual complex systems, cloud computing, large data systems, fast data systems, artificial intelligence systems;

d) Measures to ensure physical security include special isolation, anti -data leak, anti -collection, and access control.

3. Competence to assess cybersecurity conditions for important information systems on national security is prescribed as follows:

a) Forces in charge of network security protection under the Ministry of Public Security evaluated and certified to be eligible for cybersecurity for important information systems on national security, except for the case specified at Points b and pointsc this Clause;

b) Forces in charge of network security protection under the Ministry of Defense evaluated and certified to be eligible for cybersecurity for military information systems;

c) The Government Cipher Committee evaluates and certifies the conditions of network security for the Cipher's information system of the Government Cipher Committee.

4. Important information system for national security is put into operation and used after being certified to be eligible for network security.

5. The Government details Clause 2 of this Article.

Kiểm tra an ninh mạng đối với hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia

1. Kiểm tra an ninh mạng là hoạt động xác định thực trạng an ninh mạng của hệ thống thông tin, cơ sở hạ tầng hệ thống thông tin hoặc thông tin được   lưu trữ, xử lý, truyền đưa trong hệ thống thông tin nhằm phòng ngừa, phát hiện, xử lý nguy cơ đe dọa an ninh mạng và đưa ra các phương án, biện pháp bảo đảm hoạt động bình thường của hệ thống thông tin.

2. Kiểm tra an ninh mạng đối với hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia được thực hiện trong trường hợp sau đây:

a) Khi đưa phương tiện điện tử, dịch vụ an toàn thông tin mạng vào sử dụng trong hệ thống thông tin;

b) Khi có thay đổi hiện trạng hệ thống thông tin;

c) Kiểm tra định kỳ hằng năm;

d) Kiểm tra đột xuất khi xảy ra sự cố an ninh mạng, hành vi xâm phạm   an ninh mạng; khi có yêu cầu quản lý nhà nước về an ninh mạng; khi hết thời hạn khắc phục điểm yếu, lỗ hổng bảo mật theo khuyến cáo của lực lượng   chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng.

3. Đối tượng kiểm tra an ninh mạng đối với hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia bao gồm:

a) Hệ thống phần cứng, phần mềm, thiết bị số được sử dụng trong hệ thống thông tin;

b) Quy định, biện pháp bảo vệ an ninh mạng;

c) Thông tin được lưu trữ, xử lý, truyền đưa trong hệ thống thông tin;

d) Phương án ứng phó, khắc phục sự cố an ninh mạng của chủ quản hệ thống thông tin;

đ) Biện pháp bảo vệ bí mật nhà nước và phòng, chống lộ, mất bí mật    nhà nước qua các kênh kỹ thuật;

e) Nhân lực bảo vệ an ninh mạng.

4. Chủ quản hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia có       trách nhiệm kiểm tra an ninh mạng đối với hệ thống thông tin thuộc phạm vi quản lý trong trường hợp quy định tại các điểm a, b và c khoản 2 Điều này; thông báo kết quả kiểm tra bằng văn bản trước tháng 10 hằng năm cho lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thuộc Bộ Công an hoặc lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thuộc Bộ Quốc phòng đối với hệ thống thông tin quân sự.

5. Kiểm tra an ninh mạng đột xuất đối với hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia được quy định như sau:

a) Trước thời điểm tiến hành kiểm tra, lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ     an ninh mạng có trách nhiệm thông báo bằng văn bản cho chủ quản hệ thống thông tin ít nhất là 12 giờ trong trường hợp xảy ra sự cố an ninh mạng, hành vi xâm phạm an ninh mạng; ít nhất là 72 giờ trong trường hợp có yêu cầu quản lý nhà nước về an ninh mạng hoặc hết thời hạn khắc phục điểm yếu, lỗ hổng bảo mật theo khuyến cáo của lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng;

b) Trong thời hạn 30 ngày kể từ ngày kết thúc kiểm tra, lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thông báo kết quả kiểm tra và đưa ra yêu cầu đối với chủ quản hệ thống thông tin trong trường hợp phát hiện điểm yếu,       lỗ hổng bảo mật; hướng dẫn hoặc tham gia khắc phục khi có đề nghị của chủ quản hệ thống thông tin;

c) Lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thuộc Bộ Công an     kiểm tra an ninh mạng đột xuất đối với hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia, trừ hệ thống thông tin quân sự do Bộ Quốc phòng quản lý, hệ thống thông tin cơ yếu thuộc Ban Cơ yếu Chính phủ và sản phẩm mật mã do Ban Cơ yếu Chính phủ cung cấp để bảo vệ thông tin thuộc bí mật nhà nước.

Lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thuộc Bộ Quốc phòng kiểm tra an ninh mạng đột xuất đối với hệ thống thông tin quân sự.

Ban Cơ yếu Chính phủ kiểm tra an ninh mạng đột xuất đối với hệ thống thông tin cơ yếu thuộc Ban Cơ yếu Chính phủ và sản phẩm mật mã do Ban Cơ yếu Chính phủ cung cấp để bảo vệ thông tin thuộc bí mật nhà nước;

d) Chủ quản hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia có     trách nhiệm phối hợp với lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng tiến hành kiểm tra an ninh mạng đột xuất.

6. Kết quả kiểm tra an ninh mạng được bảo mật theo quy định của pháp luật.

Response and overcome network security incidents for important national security information systems

1. Activities of response and troubleshooting of cybersecurity incidents for important information systems on national security include:

a) Detecting and determining network security incidents;

b) Protect the scene, collect evidence;

c) Sembs and limitations of the scope of network security incidents, limit damage caused by cybersecurity incidents;

d) Determining objectives, subjects and scope to rescue;

d) verify, analyze, evaluate and classify network security problems;

e) Implement plans to respond and overcome network security incidents;

g) verify the cause and trace the origin;

h) Investigate and handle in accordance with the law.

2. Owner of important information systems on national security formulating plans to respond and overcome network security incidents for information systems under the management scope;Implement plans to respond and overcome when a cyber security incident occurs and promptly report to the competent network security protection force.

3. Coordinating activities to respond and overcome network security incidents for important national security information systems prescribed as follows:

a) Forces in charge of network security protection under the Ministry of Public Security shall assume the prime responsibility for coordinating the coordination of response and troubleshooting of cybersecurity incidents to the important information system on national security, except for cases.specified at Points b and c this Clause;participate in response and troubleshooting network security incidents for important information systems on national security when required;notify the manager of the information system when detecting cyber attacks and network security incidents;

b) Forces in charge of network security protection under the Ministry of Defense shall assume the prime responsibility for coordinating the coordination of response and troubleshooting of cybersecurity incidents to the military information system;

c) The Government Cipher Committee shall assume the prime responsibility for coordinating the coordination of the response and troubleshooting of cybersecurity incidents to occur with the cipher information system of the Government Cipher Committee.

4. Agencies, organizations and individuals are responsible for participating in response and troubleshooting cyber security incidents occurring with important information systems on national security when required by the force presiding over the Article.coordination.

Network spy prevention;Protect information belonging to state secrets, work secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life in cyberspace

1. Network spy acts;infringing on state secrets, work secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life on cyberspace including:

a) appropriating, trading, seizing, intentionally revealing information belonging to the state secrets, working secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life, affecting.to honor, prestige, dignity, rights and legitimate interests of agencies, organizations and individuals;

b) Deliberately erasing, damaging, lost, changing information belonging to state secrets, working secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life transmitted., stored on cyberspace;

c) Deliberately changing, canceling or disabling technical measures built, applied to protect information belonging to state secrets, work, business secrets, personal secrets,Family secret and private life;

d) Putting up to the cyber space with information belonging to state secrets, working secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life in contravention of law;

d) Deliberately listening, recording and illegal recording of conversations;

e) Other acts intentionally infringe on state secrets, work secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life.

2. The manager of the following responsible information system:

a) Checking network security in order to detect and eliminate malicious code, toxic hardware, overcome weaknesses and security holes;Detecting, preventing and handling illegal intrusion activities or other risks threatening cyber security;

b) Deploying management and technical measures to prevent, detect and prevent network spy acts, violate state secrets, work secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, secretsfamily and private life on the information system and promptly remove information related to this behavior;

c) Coordinate and comply with the requirements of cybersecurity forces on network spy prevention, information protection of state secrets, work, business secrets, personal secrets,Family secret and private life on the information system.

3. The agency drafting and storing information and documents belonging to the State secrets is responsible for protecting the State secrets that are drafted and stored on other computers, equipment or exchanging on cyberspace according to regulations.The law on the protection of state secrets.

4. The Ministry of Public Security has the following responsibility, except for the provisions of Clauses 5 and 6 of this Article:

a) Check network security for important information systems on national security in order to detect and eliminate malicious code, toxic hardware, overcome weaknesses and security holes;detect, prevent and handle illegal penetration activities;

b) Check network security for equipment, products, communication services, digital equipment, electronic equipment before putting into use in important information systems on national security;

c) Monitoring network security for important information systems on national security in order to detect and handle illegal collection of information belonging to state secrets;

d) Detecting and handling acts of illegal posting, storing and exchanging information and documents with contents of state secrets on cyberspace;

d) Participate in researching and producing storage products, transmitting information and documents with contents of state secrets;products encrypt information on cyberspace according to the assigned functions and tasks;

e) Inspecting and examining the protection of state secrets on the cyberspace of state agencies and protecting the network security of the management system important information on national security;

g) Organize training, training to raise awareness and knowledge about protecting state secrets on cyberspace, preventing and combating cyber attacks, protecting cybersecurity for cybersecurity forces.Determined in Clause 2, Article 30 of this Law.

5. The Ministry of Defense is responsible for implementing the contents prescribed at Points a, b, c, d, dd and e, Clause 4 of this Article for the military information system.

6. The Government Cipher Committee is responsible for organizing the implementation of the provisions of the law in the use of coding to protect information belonging to the State secrets stored and exchanged in cyberspace.

Prevention and control of acts of using cyberspace, information technology, electronic means to violate the law on national security, social order and safety

1. Acts of using cyberspace, information technology, electronic means to violate the law on national security, social order and safety include:

a) Posting and distributing information on cyberspace with contents specified in Clauses 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5, Article 16 and acts specified in Clause 1, Article 17 of this Law;

b) appropriating property;organize gambling and gambling via the Internet;Theft of international telecommunications on the internet;infringing copyright and intellectual property in cyberspace;

c) Forging electronic information pages of agencies, organizations and individuals;fake, circulate, steal, buy, sell, collect and illegally exchange credit card information, bank accounts of others;illegal issuance, supply and use of payment facilities;

d) Propagating, advertising, trading of goods and services on the list of prohibited as prescribed by law;

d) Guide others to commit violations of law;

e) Other acts of using cyberspace, information technology, electronic means to violate the law on national security, social order and safety.

2. Forces in charge of protecting cybersecurity are responsible for preventing and combating acts of using cyberspace, information technology, electronic means to violate the law on national security, order and safetysociety.

Network attack and control

1. Cyber ​​attacks and acts related to cyber attacks include:

a) Dispersing informatics programs that are harmful to telecommunication networks, internet, computer networks, information systems, information processing and control systems, databases, electronic means;

b) Intermittate, disorder, paralysis, interruption, stagnation of operation, illegal preventing data transmission of telecommunications networks, internet, computer networks, information systems, processing systemsphysics and control of information and electronic means;

c) Invasion, damage and appropriation of data stored, transmitted via telecommunications network, Internet, computer network, information system, processing system and control of information, databases, electronic means;

d) Invasive, create or exploit weaknesses, security holes and system services to appropriate information and benefit illicit profits;

d) Manufacturing, trading, exchanging, giving tools, equipment, software features Telecommunications network, internet, computer network, information system, processing system and controlnews, databases, electronic means for use for illegal purposes;

e) Other behaviors affecting the normal operation of telecommunication networks, internet, computer networks, information systems, information processing and control systems, databases, electronic means.

2. The information system owner is responsible for applying technical measures to prevent and prevent acts specified at Points a, B, C, D and E, Clause 1 of this Article for the information systemScope of management.

3. When cyber attacks occur violating or threatening to infringe on sovereignty, interests, national security, seriously damage social order and safety, specialized forces in charge of network security to preside over, coordinating with the manager of the information system and related organizations and individuals to apply measures to determine the origin of cyber attacks and collect evidence;Request businesses to provide services on telecommunications networks, internet, and services on the network space to block information to prevent, eliminate cyber attacks and provide adequate and timely information, related document.

4. Responsibility for prevention and control of cyber attacks is prescribed as follows:

a) The Ministry of Public Security shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the concerned ministries and branches to conduct the prevention, detection and handling of acts specified in Clause 1 of this Article to infringe up or threaten violations of sovereignty and interests., national security, seriously damage social order and safety nationwide, except for the case specified at Points b and c this Clause;

b) The Ministry of Defense shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the concerned ministries and branches in carrying out the prevention, detection and handling of acts specified in Clause 1 of this Article for the military information system;

c) The Government Cipher Committee shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the concerned ministries and branches to conduct the prevention, detection and handling of behaviors specified in Clause 1 of this Article for the cipher information system under the CommitteeCipher Government.

Phòng ngừa, xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng

1. Tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng bao gồm:

a) Xuất hiện thông tin kích động trên không gian mạng có nguy cơ xảy ra bạo loạn, phá rối an ninh, khủng bố;

b) Tấn công vào hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia;

c) Tấn công nhiều hệ thống thông tin trên quy mô lớn, cường độ cao;

d) Tấn công mạng nhằm phá hủy công trình quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia, mục tiêu quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia;

đ) Tấn công mạng xâm phạm nghiêm trọng chủ quyền, lợi ích, an ninh quốc gia; gây tổn hại đặc biệt nghiêm trọng trật tự, an toàn xã hội, quyền và lợi ích hợp pháp của cơ quan, tổ chức, cá nhân.

2. Trách nhiệm phòng ngừa tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng được quy định như sau:

a) Lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng phối hợp với chủ quản hệ thống thông tin quan trọng về an ninh quốc gia triển khai các giải pháp kỹ thuật, nghiệp vụ để phòng ngừa, phát hiện, xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng;

b) Doanh nghiệp viễn thông, Internet, công nghệ thông tin, doanh nghiệp cung cấp dịch vụ trên mạng viễn thông, mạng Internet, các dịch vụ gia tăng trên không gian mạng và cơ quan, tổ chức, cá nhân có liên quan có trách nhiệm   phối hợp với lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thuộc Bộ Công an trong phòng ngừa, phát hiện, xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng.

3. Biện pháp xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng bao gồm:

a) Triển khai ngay phương án phòng ngừa, ứng phó khẩn cấp về an ninh mạng, ngăn chặn, loại trừ hoặc giảm nhẹ thiệt hại do tình huống  nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng gây ra;

b) Thông báo đến cơ quan, tổ chức, cá nhân có liên quan;

c) Thu thập thông tin liên quan; theo dõi, giám sát liên tục đối với  tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng;

d) Phân tích, đánh giá thông tin, dự báo khả năng, phạm vi ảnh hưởng và mức độ thiệt hại do tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng gây ra;

đ) Ngừng cung cấp thông tin mạng tại khu vực cụ thể hoặc ngắt cổng kết nối mạng quốc tế;

e) Bố trí lực lượng, phương tiện ngăn chặn, loại bỏ tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng;

g) Biện pháp khác theo quy định của Luật An ninh quốc gia.

4. Việc xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng được quy định như sau:

a) Khi phát hiện tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng, cơ quan, tổ chức, cá nhân kịp thời thông báo cho lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng và áp dụng ngay các biện pháp quy định tại điểm a và điểm b khoản 3 Điều này;

b) Thủ tướng Chính phủ xem xét, quyết định hoặc ủy quyền cho Bộ trưởng Bộ Công an xem xét, quyết định, xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng trong phạm vi cả nước hoặc từng địa phương hoặc đối với một mục tiêu cụ thể.

Thủ tướng Chính phủ xem xét, quyết định hoặc ủy quyền cho Bộ trưởng Bộ Quốc phòng xem xét, quyết định, xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng đối với hệ thống thông tin quân sự và hệ thống thông tin cơ yếu thuộc  Ban Cơ yếu Chính phủ;

c) Lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng chủ trì, phối hợp với cơ quan, tổ chức, cá nhân có liên quan áp dụng các biện pháp quy định tại khoản 3 Điều này để xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng;

d) Cơ quan, tổ chức, cá nhân có liên quan có trách nhiệm phối hợp với lực lượng chuyên trách bảo vệ an ninh mạng thực hiện biện pháp nhằm ngăn chặn, xử lý tình huống nguy hiểm về an ninh mạng.

Struggle to protect network security

1. The struggle to protect network security is an organized activity implemented by a specialized force for cybersecurity on cyberspace to protect national security and ensure social order and safety.

2. Contents of the struggle to protect network security include:

a) Organizing the grasp of the situation related to national security protection activities;

b) Prevention and control of attacks and stable activities of important information systems on national security;

c) Paralys or limit cyber spatial use in order to cause national security harm or cause particularly serious damage to social order and safety;

d) Actively attack disabling goals on cyberspace to protect national security and ensure social order and safety.

3. The Ministry of Public Security shall assume the prime responsibility for, and coordinate with the concerned ministries and branches to struggle to protect network security.

Deploying activities to protect cybersecurity in state agencies and political organizations at the central and local levels

1. Contents of implementing network security protection activities include:

a) Develop and complete regulations and regulations on using internal computer networks, computer networks with internet connection;plan to ensure network security for the information system;plans to respond and overcome network security incidents;

b) Application and implementation of plans, measures and technologies to protect cybersecurity for information and information systems, documents stored, drafted and transmitted on information systems within the scope ofphysical;

c) Organizing fostering knowledge of cybersecurity for cadres, civil servants, officials and employees;improve network security protection for network security forces;

d) Protect cybersecurity in providing public services on cyberspace, providing, exchanging, collecting information with agencies, organizations, individuals, sharing internal information and with the opportunityother officials or in other activities as prescribed by the Government;

d) Investing and building facilities in accordance with conditions to ensure the implementation of network security protection activities for the information system;

e) Checking network security for the information system;prevention and control of violations of the law on cybersecurity;respond and overcome network security incidents.

2. The heads of agencies and organizations shall have to implement cybersecurity protection activities under their management.

Research and development of cybersecurity

1. Content of research and development of network security includes:

a) Building software systems, network security equipment;

b) Methods of software evaluation, network security protection equipment meets the standards and limits the existence of weaknesses, security holes, malware;

c) Methods of hardware and software testing are provided with the function;

d) Methods of protecting state secrets, working secrets, business secrets, personal secrets, family secrets and private life;security ability when transmitting information on cyberspace;

d) Determining the origin of the information transmitted on cyberspace;

e) Solve the risk of cyber security threat;

g) Building network sports, network security testing environment;

h) Technical initiatives to raise awareness and skills on network security;

i) Forecast of network security;

k) Practical research, developing cybersecurity theory.

2. Relevant agencies, organizations and individuals have the right to research and develop cybersecurity.

Improve cybersecurity capacity

1. The State encourages and creates favorable conditions for agencies, organizations and individuals to improve their ability to autonomy in cybersecurity and improve the ability to produce, inspect, evaluate and test digital equipment and translationNetwork crop, network application.

2. The Government implements the following measures to improve the capacity of cybersecurity for agencies, organizations and individuals:

a) Promote the transfer, research, master and develop technology, products, services and applications to protect network security;

b) Promote the application of new technology and advanced technology related to cybersecurity;

c) Organize training, development and use of cybersecurity human resources;

d) Strengthen the business environment, improve competitive conditions to support businesses to research and produce products, services and applications to protect network security.

Responsibility of the Ministry of Public Security

The Ministry of Public Security is responsible to the Government to perform the state management of cybersecurity and have the following duties and powers, except for the content of the Ministry of Defense and the Government Cipher Committee:

1. To promulgate or submit to competent state agencies to promulgate and guide the implementation of legal documents on cybersecurity;

2. Develop and propose strategies, guidelines, policies, plans and plans to protect network security;

3. Preventing and struggling with cyber spaces violating sovereignty, interests, national security, social order and safety and cybercrime prevention;

4. Ensuring information security on cyberspace;Develop a mechanism to authenticate the number of account registration information;Warning, sharing network security information, risk of cyber security threats;

5. To advise and propose the Government and the Prime Minister to consider and decide the assignment and coordination of the implementation of network security protection measures, prevention and handling of cybersecurity violations in the school.convergence of state management related to the scope of management of many ministries and branches;

6. Organizing drills to prevent and combat cyber attacks;rehearsal response and troubleshooting of network security incidents for important information systems on national security;

7. Checking, inspecting and settling complaints, denunciations and handling violations of cybersecurity laws.

Responsibility of the Ministry of Defense

The Ministry of Defense is responsible to the Government to perform state management of cyber security within the management scope and have the following tasks and powers:

1. To promulgate or submit to the competent state agency to promulgate and guide the implementation of legal documents on cyber security within the scope of management;

2. Develop and propose strategies, guidelines, policies, plans and plans to protect network security within the management scope;

3. Preventing and struggling with cyberspace activities that violate national security within the management scope;

4. Coordinating with the Ministry of Public Security to organize drills to prevent and combat cyber attacks, response drills, troubleshooting network security incidents for important information systems on national security and public implementationnetwork security protection;

5. Checking, inspecting, settling complaints, denunciations and handling violations of cybersecurity laws within the scope of management.

The responsibility of the service provider in cyberspace

1. Enterprises providing services on cyberspace in Vietnam are responsible for the following:

a) Warning the possibility of insecurity in the use of services on the cyberspace provided and guided to prevent preventive measures;

b) Develop plans and solutions to respond quickly to cybersecurity incidents, immediately handle weaknesses, security holes, malware, cyber attacks, network intrusion and other security risks;When a network security incident occurred, immediately implemented an emergency plan, appropriate response measures, and reported to a specialized force to protect network security in accordance with this Law;

c) Applying technical solutions and other necessary measures to ensure the security of information collection, preventing the risk of revealing, leaking, damaging or losing data;In case of occurrence or a risk of incidents of revealing, falling, damaging or losing data of users, it is necessary to immediately offer solutions to respond, and notify the user and report it tospecialized forces to protect network security in accordance with this Law;

d) Coordinate and create conditions for specialized forces to protect network security in network security protection.

2. Enterprises providing services on telecommunications networks, internet, and increasing services on cyberspace in Vietnam are responsible for implementing the provisions of Clause 1 of this Article, Clause 2 and Clause 3, Article 26 of the LawThis.

