The authority of the Arbitration Council applies temporary emergency measures

1. At the request of one of the parties, the Arbitration Council may apply one or several temporary emergency measures to the disputed parties.

2. Temporary emergency measures include:

a) Prohibit changing the current status of disputes;

b) Prohibiting or forcing any dispute party to perform one or several certain acts to prevent acts adversely affecting the arbitration processing process;

c) Disposal of disputed assets;

d) Requires to preserve, store, sell or dispose of any property of one or disputed parties;

d) Temporary request for payment between the parties;

e) Prohibit the transfer of property rights to the disputed property.

3. In the process of resolving disputes, if one of the parties requested the Court to apply one or a number of temporary emergency measures specified in Clause 2 of this Article, then there is an application to the CouncilTai applied temporary emergency measures, the arbitration council must refuse.

4. Before applying temporary emergency measures, the Arbitration Council has the right to force the party to request the application of temporary emergency measures to fulfill the financial security obligations.

5. The Arbitration Council applies other temporary emergency measures or exceeds the requirement of applying the provision of the required provider, causing damage to the required party, the application or the third personThe victim has the right to sue to the Court to request the settlement of compensation in accordance with the law on civil proceedings.

Procedures for application of temporary emergency measures of the Council of Arbitration

