3. According to the decision of the Arbitration Council, the party requires the application of temporary emergency measures to send an amount of money, precious metal, gem or valuable papers set by the arbitration council corresponding to the price.Treatment of damage may arise due to improperly applied emergency measures to protect the interests of the party required to apply temporary emergency measures.The amount of money, precious metal, gemstones or valuable papers sent to the blockade account at the bank is decided by the Arbitration Council.

4. Within 03 working days from the date of receipt, right after the requesting party has implemented a measure to ensure the provisions of Clause 3 of this Article, the arbitration Council shall consider and issue a decision to apply the measure.Temporary emergency.In case of failure to accept the request, the Arbitration Council notifies it in writing and clearly states the reason for the requesting party.

5. The implementation of the decision on the application of temporary emergency measures of the Arbitration Council shall comply with the law on civil judgment execution.

Suspension Suspension

1. The dispute is suspended in the following cases:

a) The plaintiff or defendant is an individual who has died but their rights and obligations are not inherited;

b) The plaintiff or defendant is the agency or organization has terminated the operation, bankruptcy, dissolution, consolidation, merger, division, separation or conversion of organizational forms without agencies or organizationswho receive the rights and obligations of such agencies and organizations;

c) The plaintiff withdraws the petition or is considered to have withdrawn the petition according to the provisions of Clause 1, Article 56 of this Law, except for cases where the defendant is required to continue resolving the dispute;

d) The parties agree to terminate the dispute settlement;

d) The Court has decided that the dispute is not under the jurisdiction of the arbitration council, without an arbitration agreement, an invalid arbitration agreement or an arbitration agreement cannot be implemented in accordance with Clause 644 of this law.

2. The arbitration council issues a decision to suspend the dispute.In case the Arbitration Council has not been established, the Chairman of the Arbitration Center shall issue a decision to suspend the dispute.

