International cooperation on youth

1. International cooperation on youth must ensure the principle of equality, respect for independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity, in accordance with the laws of each country, international treaties that the Socialist Republic of the Socialist RepublicVietnam is a member and international practice.

2. Content of international cooperation on youth includes:

a) Participate in international organizations;signing and implementing international treaties and international agreements on young people;International cooperation programs and projects on young people;

b) Exchange of information, management experience and policies and laws on youth;

c) Exchange between Vietnamese youth and young people in other countries.

Policies for young volunteers

1. Youth volunteers are the shocking force of young people participating in the implementation of socio -economic development tasks, job creation, education, training, youth training and unexpected tasks., urgent, difficult and arduous in national construction and defense.

2. The State promulgates policies for young people to volunteer to perform the following tasks:

a) Participate in the socio -economic development project assigned by the State;

b) Participate in overcoming consequences of natural disasters and epidemics;environmental protection;maintain social order and safety, national defense and national security;

c) Participate in the production of goods, service provision, transfer of technical advances to support production and vocational training associated with creating jobs for young people;

d) Unexpected, urgent, difficult and arduous tasks as prescribed by law.

3. The State ensures the conditions for funding, facilities and equipment necessary for the volunteer youth organization when performing the task assigned by the State.

4. Youth volunteers are entitled to the regime and policies during and after completing the task.

